<headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 16 at 1:04AM MDT  by NWS Glasgow</headline>
<description>...A strong thunderstorm will impact portions of southeastern
Richland County through 200 AM MDT...
At 104 AM MDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Sidney, moving east at 15 mph.
HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph and pea size hail.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor damage to outdoor objects is
possible.
Locations impacted include...
Sidney, Fairview, Midway, Wooley and Crane.
MAX HAIL SIZE...0.25 IN
MAX WIND GUST...50 MPH</description>
<instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
